after parsing:

1) Build procedure table
- first pass: collect procedure declarations/signatures (names, inputs, outputs)
- second pass: define procedures

2) Define procedures
- procedure definition means building the jump tables and basic blocks that compose a procedure
- you will need two passes, since jumps can be bidirectional
- first pass builds jump table and blocks
- second pass does typechecks, over/underflow checks, jump checks, etc
- remember jumps may not pass procedure boundaries
